&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-5702&quot; title=&quot;Text in a certain font is lost when converting pdf to image&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-5702&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-5702&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: output warning, don&apos;t throw exception for bad kerning subtable&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17777054" author="jira-bot" created="Thu, 19 Oct 2023 06:35:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1913107 from Tilman Hausherr in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1913107&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1913107&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-5702&quot; title=&quot;Text in a certain font is lost when converting pdf to image&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-5702&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-5702&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: output warning, don&apos;t throw exception for bad kerning subtable&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17777055" author="tilman" created="Thu, 19 Oct 2023 06:36:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks. The problem is that after the actual font failed, the fallback font didn&apos;t have the glyphs needed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17777074" author="JIRAUSER297279" created="Thu, 19 Oct 2023 07:09:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you for your prompt response to this issue&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17777139" author="JIRAUSER297279" created="Thu, 19 Oct 2023 09:01:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;image-wrap&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/13063687/13063687_screenshot-1.png&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px solid black&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;br/&gt;
Can we customize the guaranteed font scheme?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17777349" author="tilman" created="Thu, 19 Oct 2023 16:12:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You could try to call FontMappers.set() with your own fontmapper. But I don&apos;t think you&apos;ll be happy with it. There might be weird effects if your new fallback font is broken in ways that you didn&apos;t imagine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Btw the reason that PDFBox couldn&apos;t find a replacement font is because the font had the name &quot;CIDFont-F5&quot; instead of the name of the actual font (which was Yahei Light)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
